headline: Dow Inc. price target lowered to $29 from $41 at UBS
summary: UBS analyst Joshua Spector lowered the firm’s price target on Dow Inc. (DOW) to $29 from $41 and keeps a Neutral rating on the shares. The firm sees another challenging earnings cycle, with “largely ok” downstream earnings, while upstream/commodity earnings will be impacted by higher costs and likely weaker end of quarter demand, the analyst tells investors in a research note. UBS sees earnings misses to drive stocks down vs. provide relief. Published first on TheFly – the ultimate source for re
